  head
    head
        meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no")

    title Bar44
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap.min.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='/stylesheets/steez.css')
  body
    #home
    #background-img-container
        img(src='images/mountain-snow.jpg' id='background-img1')
        img(src='images/zr-structure-1.jpg' id='background-img2')
        img(src='images/zr-structure-3.jpg' id='background-img3')
    #logo-box
        .logo-top
        .logo 44
    nav(role="navigation").navbar.navbar-inverse.navbar-fixed-top.nav
        .navbar-header
            button(type="button", data-toggle="collapse", data-target=".navbar-ex1-collapse").navbar-toggle
                span.sr-only Toggle navigation
                span.icon-bar
                span.icon-bar
                span.icon-bar
        .collapse.navbar-collapse.navbar-ex1-collapse
            ul.nav.navbar-nav.list-inline
                li.home.active: a(href='#home' data-scroll) Home
                li.about: a(href='#about' data-scroll) Me
                li.work: a(href='#work' data-scroll) Build
                li.contact: a(href='#contact' data-scroll) Contact
    .bottom-left-mask
    .top-trigger.about-trigger
    #about.content
        .container
            .bottom-trigger.about-trigger
            .row.head-about
                .col-sm-4
                    h1 I Am.
            .row.content-body-about
                .col-sm-2.col-sm-offset-1
                    img(src='images/michael-profile.jpg').profile-pic.img-circle
                .col-sm-6.col-sm-offset-2
                    .row
                        h1 Michael Lechner
                        h4.text-muted.sub-title web developer
                        p 
                            | Born in Durango, Graduated from Michigan State, 
                            | Played in Yosemite and Landed in Boulder, CO.
                        p    
                            | Away from the keyboard,
                            | I love the adventure of the mountains and the 
                            | American West.
                            | Although I come from a lineage of cattle ranchers, I am
                            | much more comfortable wrangling curly brackets than
                            | steers. When people ask what I do, I tell them I 
                            | write cowboy code. 
                        p
                            | Refactoring the old and embracing 
                            | the new, I have a thing for technology and have 
                            | spent time working on all levels of the web stack. 
                            | Most recently I have been eating Javascript for breakfast,
                            | lunch and dinner and I am excited to be a part of 
                            | pushing this language into the future
                    .row.tech-imgs
                        img(src='images/html5-256.png').html5-img
                        img(src='images/js-240.png').js-img
                        img(src='images/nodejs-light.png').node-img
            .row.content-body-about
    .top-left-mask
    .spacer
    .bottom-left-mask
    .top-trigger.work-trigger
    #work.content
        .container
            .bottom-trigger.work-trigger
            .row.head-work
                .col-sm-4
                    h1 I Build Things.
            .row.portfolio.content-body-work
                .col-sm-2.col-sm-offset-1.port-item
                    img(src='images/avy-rose.png').img-circle.port-img
                    h3 
                        a(href='https://github.com/michael-lechner/avy-rose') Avy Rose
                    p an interactive mobile application using data from the CAIC
                .col-sm-2.port-item
                    img(src='images/whosays.png').img-circle.port-img
                    h3 
                        a(href='http://whosays.herokuapp.com') Who Says
                    p a browser based version of your favorite memory game
                .col-sm-2.port-item
                    img(src='images/ama-deus.png').img-circle.port-img
                    h3 Ama Deus
                    p a site in progress during the spring of 2014
            .row.content-body-work    
                .col-sm-9.col-sm-offset-6
                    h2.text-muted.more more to come...    
    .top-left-mask
    .spacer
    .bottom-left-mask.dark
    .top-trigger.contact-trigger
    #contact.content
        .container
            .row.head-contact
                .col-sm-6
                    h1 Say Hello.
            .row.form-row.content-body-contact
                .col-sm-6
                    p 
                        | Thanks for taking the time and having a look around! Unfortunately, this is a website
                        | and I can't shake your hand, but if I could I would. 
                    p
                        | If you have an idea and you think I could help or if you would 
                        | just like to chat,
                        | please drop me a line and let me know a little bit more about
                        | what's on your mind or what we could build together.
                    .li-icon
                        a(href='http://www.linkedin.com/pub/michael-lechner/17/3b7/7b4/')
                            img(src='/images/li-blue.png')
                            img(src='/images/li-black.png')
                    .gh-icon 
                        a(href='https://github.com/michael-lechner/whosays')
                            img(src='images/git-blue.png')
                            img(src='images/git-black.png')
                    .em-icon    
                        a(href='mailto:mlechner2@gmail.com?Subject=bar44?').glyphicon.glyphicon-envelope

                .col-sm-6
                    form(role='form').email-form
                        .form-group.email-group
                            input(type='email' placeholder='Your Email Here.').form-control.email-address
                        .form-group.message-group
                            textarea(type='text' placeholder='Your Message Here.').form-control.message
                        button.btn.btn-lg.btn-default.btn-right.pull-right.submit-contact send
    .top-left-mask.dark

